summary.snippet: "The service here was excellent, staff super friendly Food absolutely delicious!"
"Great breakfast and brunch place for gluten free options."
"Ordered scrambled light but received over cooked very dry eggs."

most_relevant.description: Everything was good here! The atmosphere is really cute, clean and inviting. The service was friendly and attentive. The food tasted FRESH and wholesome. Lots of vegan and gluten-free options. Great breakfast place worth a trip and many returns!

Anna’s is my favorite restaurant, today for the first time me and my family of four got to go orders instead of dining in like we usually do. We put our order in at 2 p.m. they close at 3 one of the reasons we got to go. I ordered candied pecan and banana French toast for my young son 7 and a monte cristo for my husband, both of which were just plain bread, not dipped in French toast egg batter. As you can imagine, my 7 year old wouldn’t eat his food. If this had been a cheap place I wouldn’t leave a negative review, but I’m honestly so flabbergasted that they would just put some slices of plain bread in a to go box with some toppings and I paid 16 dollars for this.  I usually am amazed with everything Anna’s is, the food, the service , everything is usually great and is why it is my favorite  restaurant and is usually worth the prices. Today I am beyond disappointed, being in the service industry myself I would never serve food like this to someone. Attaching pictures of their stock photo and what I received.

Seriously, this place has THE best brunch around!  It's always busy, and there is a reason for that.  We met our college-aged daughter for her birthday and were not disappointed!  The chicken and waffles are perfection (pictured below), along with the Billion Dollar Bacon and Cinnamon Monkey Bread for table starters.  The entire menu looks great!  We will be back to try some more.

despite a very long line and an expected 30 min - 1 hour wait, we were seated quickly and our food came out so fast! Lail was amazing and helped me so kindly after I ordered my meal incorrectly. She was so patient and understanding. As a vegan, it’s hard to find worthwhile breakfast restaurants but the food here is SO worth the price and there truly is something for everyone. Truly a special place that we are happy to be able to bring friends and family to.

We loved the environment of Anna’s House. It takes you back to grandma’s where we usually have our best memories. The food was great and the place was packed. Service was also pretty good but it took a little bit long, sometimes. Overall, It is an awesome place to have a breakfast or even brunch. Not expensive for what it provides.

Alex my server was simply amazing, quick service and told us about the resident ducks that require feeding for breakfast and lunch :)
The food is always good here, I love all of their options of food. Gluten free to plant based.  Omelet was awesome and alot of good food.

Their decorations are great as well  I love the retro look and feel to the whole place.

My go to destination for brunch on any lazy sunday. From its warm and inviting ambience to its mouthwatering menu offerings this place has my heart! My personal favorite is Cappuccino with a dash of hazelnut and eggs benedict. My husband loves their range of omelettes and my kid absolutely relishes their french toasts and pancakes

Such a great experience here 💛💙 Modern home style Breakfast place. Atmosphere is great food are good portion size the price is even better than many place compare to the plate and decor on it. Coffee here is on point for me hot and cold. Recommend for anyone that love the nice relax place for little meet up or family meals. The location is in the middle of everything from highway, mall, convenient store or even downtown. Great place!
📍I will be regular here for sure!
